modules.description: This module provides a command-line parsing function `main` that initializes HTTP clients and handles common tool options like cache directories, certificate paths, and HTTP backend selection. It works with standard OCaml data types such as string lists, Arg specifications, and Lwt promises, along with the Ldp.Http.Http module for handling HTTP requests. It is used to build command-line tools that interact with HTTP services, particularly in the context of Linked Data Platform operations.

The module includes a command-line parsing function `main` that initializes HTTP clients and manages options like cache directories, certificate paths, and HTTP backends. It operates with string lists, Arg specifications, Lwt promises, and the Ldp.Http.Http module. This module is used to develop command-line tools for interacting with HTTP services in Linked Data Platform workflows.
